features: Stack Your Style: This bedside table set includes two stackable side tables that can be arranged together or separately to maximize your living space. Stack them together to create a 25.3″ tall table with 3 levels of storage with easy access to the open shelving.

Premium Bamboo Wood: Crafted from high-quality bamboo, these Pipishell nightstands are exceptionally sturdy to hold up to 22 lbs each. Bamboo wood is a sustainable material that provides both strength and durability for long-lasting use.

Perfect for Small Spaces: The bamboo side tables are designed to fit in compact living spaces. The versatile 15.7″ W x 11.4″ Dx 16.5″ H size allows you to make the most of your available space without sacrificing style or functionality.

Modular Design: Pipishell end tables can be used as coffee tables, nightstands, sofa side tables, and more. Placed in front of each other, the stackable tables can create a larger tabletop to arrange magazines and decorations in your living room or den.

Complement Your Décor: The bedside tables feature a classic bamboo finish that can add style and character to any room. Whether you prefer a modern, vintage, or traditional look, the bamboo nightstands can blend in perfectly with any décor.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Pipishell Stackable Side Tables | Complement Your Living Space Pipishell bedside tables give you the flexibility to arrange your living space to fit your style. Stack the nightstands together for a taller storage solution with 3 levels of storage or separate them to use next to a bed or sofa where a shorter tabletop works best.

Our side tables are made of 100% bamboo wood with excellent durability and water resistance. Bamboo’s strength and rapid growth makes the material a sustainable choice for quality furniture construction.

Easily cleaned with a towel The bamboo end tables can be simply wipe down the tables to remove dust and debris without using chemicals or abrasive cleaners. Open shelf design Makes these bedside tables an excellent choice for flexible storage within arm’s reach. Easily access items without opening bulky cabinets or drawers. Be stacked or used separately Stacked together, 25.3″ tall, perfect for taller beds or furniture. Used separately, 16.9″ tall to fit better next to low sofas or chairs. A-shaped legs Angled to provide maximum support. Foot pads attach to each table leg so that floors do not get scratched during use.

Pipishell nightstands boast a weight capacity of up to 22 lbs each to securely hold your household items. Display your favorite plants or decorations on the tables without worrying about table strength or stability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality, perfect size for low platform or floor bed
reviews.reviewText: This was very easy to put together. I advise if you have a drill to use it. It makes the entire thing take 5 minutes tops. Just go slow and low power. I have trouble finding nightstands that are multipurpose and also not super tall. If you want a taller one, you can certainly stack these together because their price is great too. It's not like you will be breaking the bank if you buy two sets of them. It's a very natural light wood color that goes with a lot of different prints, styles, and rooms. For the price, I feel like this was a steal. It's very sturdy and is such a step up from all the particle board stuff you see for sale.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice little tables
reviews.reviewText: Read the details when you buy. These are stackable and each individual table is small. They go together easy just pay attention to your holes and it'll build quick. The instructions leave a little to be desired. Don't love the screw holes on the top of the table but a little wood filler will cure that. Your getting a pretty low priced item so it is what it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good looking Nightstands
reviews.reviewText: The bamboo is quite hard and looks good. The finish isn't the smoothest but will work good. You need to use a hand screwdriver or you might strip a screw. The main reason for minus 1 star is I wish they were taller, like 16-1/2". For now I stacked one on top the other and worked great. The legs interlock perfectly for stacking. I plan on removing the legs and hang on the wall for floating nightstands.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Short but nice!
reviews.reviewText: Yes these nightstand/end tables are very short (check measurements before buying), but they work for a bed that has no box spring and is naturally lower to the ground. You can always stack them to get more height but we liked them just the way they were in their single fashion.The tables did not come with instructions but they were very easy to put together. It took me about 10 minutes to complete each table. They are slightly wobbly but that doesn't bother me. The bamboo is a nice color and quality. The bamboo has a good weight to it making it seem more expensive then the cost. I would highly recommend the tables as they are a good price for the quality you get.On a side note, the nightstands do match the Zinus Paul bedframe: https://www.amazon.com/Zinus-Sonoma-Metal-Platform-Support/dp/B06WWF1RLF/ref=sr_1_49?keywords=wood+bedframe+zinus&qid=1575888933&sr=8-49

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Very Small but decent
reviews.reviewText: These are very small but sturdy and easy to assemble. I ended up taking the legs off and using them for a dog step at the end of my bed. They were not suitable for end tables with their size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice! Small, Tidy, Nice looking
reviews.reviewText: Super cute! Lightweight, attractive design, endless uses. — The first thing I did was lay out all the different sections into the two separate tables to bigger top and bottom of the table, the sides and two legs for each, and then discovered their leg pads in the envelope so the first actual construction I did was to apply the Leg pads… BUT: Noticed only after applying for to one of the sets of legs that there were only six pads and the envelope. Had I known that to begin with? I think I would have cut them in half so there were enough to go around.Assembling the table: The two larger segments that belong for the top of the table, and then the bottom of the table that creates the shelf in between, the holes drilled, have a distinct difference that lets you know which side to screw the screws into. There’s a divot that is to hold the screw head on one side and the hole is not that way on the other side. There are similar distinctions on every piece of wood to show which side you want to have facing out invisible are you as you use the finish table and which side you want facing in or which side the screw should be entered into. Just check that out closely. Be sure the four small holes in the end pieces are facing out to attach the legs there. - Down side: after several weeks of use, I can see that the tabletop blemishes easily from drinking glasses on the surface just about anything that you would normally put on a table can easily make a scratch mark in it. The scratch mark comes out, kind of like a gray line and from putting glasses of water or coffee or wine or whatever on the table top it makes these whitish rings as you can see in the last photo. - be sure to to screw the top screws in tightly enough so that the table doesn’t wobble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I'm pleased with the quality. It took me about 20 minutes to assemble both of these from opening the package to tossing box into the recycling.

reviews.reviewTitle: Mucho más pequeños de lo imaginado
reviews.reviewText: Tomamos en cuenta las medidas, sin embargo, están más pequeños de lo esperado. El diseño y material es bueno, pero no son mesitas de noche para una recámara. Más bien funcionan como mesitas auxiliares para otras cosas. Muy, muy pequeñas. Valor por el precio: se nos hizo caro por lo que es y tardó en llegar.
